OL,7,FLisa De-Bargeton said her son Louis
OL,8,Fhas autism, and that his overnight
OL,9,Fstays at Pencalenick School are vital
OL,10,Fto his development.
OL,12,FMs De-Bargeton said: "It gives me an
OL,13,Fopportunity to spend time with Louis'
OL,14,Fyounger brother, and it helps
OL,15,Fobviously with his social skills and
OL,16,Flife skills."
OL,18,FLouis said: "Staying over at school is
OL,19,Fprobably my favourite thing about
OL,20,Fschool. We get to go out to stuff like
OL,21,Fthe beach, and we also did Ten Tors."
